article.headline: Coastal Carolina beats Gardner-Webb 75-60
article.story: CONWAY, S.C. -- Warren Gillis scored 18 points, leading a balanced attack, as Coastal Carolina cruised to a 75-60 win over Gardner-Webb on Saturday. Josh Cameron and Elijah Wilson both scored 16 points and Badou Diagne added 11 points and 12 boards. Gillis also recorded seven steals. Coastal Carolina (16-10, 9-3 Big South) shot 57 percent from the floor. Gardner-Webb (14-13, 7-5) was led by Donta Harper with 16 points while Jerome Hill and Tyrell Nelson both added 12. With the score tied at 16, Gardner-Webb made an 8-point run to grab the lead, then hung on to lead 28-25 at the intermission after Coastal Carolina ran off the next seven points, including a trey by Eric Smith. The Chanticleers tied the game at 52 on a pair of Josh Cameron free throws, then ran off 12 of the next 14 points to take control of the game.
